In the {{ill|Ebers calendar|de|Ebers-Kalender|qq=draft}}, dated to circa 1517 BCE, Rekeh-nedjes corresponded to the second month of {{ill|Season of the Emergence|lt=Peret|de|Peret (Altes Ägypten)|1=Season of the Emergence|lt=Peret|2=de|3=Peret (Altes Ägypten)|4=ja|5=ペレト|6=zh|7=播種季|8=ru|9=Перет|10=uk|11=Перет|qq=draft|13=Season of the Emergence|14=es|15=Estación de la emergencia|16=fr|17=Peret|18=pl|19=Peret|20=ro|21=Peret|qq=draft}} and ran from January 15 to February 13 ({{ill|Elephantine|de|Elephantine|qq=draft}}) or from January 20 to February 18 ({{ill|Memphis (Egypt)|de|Memphis (Ägypten)|qq=draft}}).
